@* Unlike UseSecurityHeaders in WebApplicationExtensions.cs, which only applies during Blazor Server
   and Blazor WebAssembly Pre-Rendering, this component works across all Interactive Blazor
   rendering modes (Server, WebAssembly, WebAssembly Standalone, Auto and Hybrid).
   Because it enforces a stricter Content-Security-Policy, it is not enabled by default.
   To activate it, add <SecurityHeaders /> inside AppShell.razor *@

@*
    Note: Even this CSP is not fully strict:
    1- It allows `inline` scripts and styles, which is not recommended. To avoid this, you can use a nonce or hash-based approach.
    2- It gets applied late in the rendering process, which means that some content might be rendered before the CSP is applied.
    You can mitigate this by moving the desired configuration in index.html files in Client.Maui & Client.Web projects.
*@

<HeadContent>
    <meta name="referrer" content="strict-origin-when-cross-origin">
    <meta http-equiv="Content-Security-Policy" content="@CspContent">
</HeadContent>